{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS","iPadOS","Mac Catalyst"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@interface"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolygon"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)MLNMultiPoint","text":"MLNMultiPoint"}]}]},{"mentions":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/GeoJSON","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/Predicates_and_Expressions"],"kind":"mentions"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can add polygon shapes to the map by adding them to an "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"object. Configure the appearance of an "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"’s or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"’s polygons collectively using an "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNSymbolStyleLayer","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object. To access a polygon’s attributes, use an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygonFeature","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, you can add a polygon overlay directly to a map view using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addAnnotation:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView\/addOverlay:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" method. Configure"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a polygon overlay’s appearance using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:strokeColorForShapeAnnotation:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapViewDelegate\/mapView:fillColorForPolygonAnnotation:","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The vertices are automatically connected in the order in which you provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"them. You should close the polygon by specifying the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as the first and last vertices; otherwise, the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"polygon’s fill may not cover the area you expect it to. To avoid filling the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"space within the shape, give the polygon a transparent fill or use an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A polygon may have one or more interior polygons, or holes, that you specify as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" objects with the "},{"code":"+polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"method. For example, if a polygon represents a lake, it could exclude an island"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"within the lake using an interior polygon. Interior polygons may not themselves"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"have interior polygons. To represent a shape that includes a polygon within a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"hole or, more generally, to group multiple polygons together in one shape, use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"an "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" object."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To make the polygon straddle the antimeridian, specify some longitudes less"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"than −180 degrees or greater than 180 degrees."}]},{"type":"heading","level":4,"text":"Related examples","anchor":"Related-examples"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TODO: Add a polygon annotation, learn how to initialize an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" object from an array of coordinates."}]}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon"]}],"metadata":{"externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNPolygon","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolygon"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNPolygon"}],"roleHeading":"Class","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"class","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"title":"MLNPolygon"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/interiorPolygons"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/polygonWithCoordinates:count:","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/polygonWithCoordinates:count:interiorPolygons:"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Methods","title":"Type Methods"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint"],"type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygonFeature"],"type":"inheritedBy","kind":"relationships","title":"Inherited By"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"],"type":"conformsTo","kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a closed shape consisting of four or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"vertices, specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances, and the edges that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connect them. For example, you could use a polygon shape to represent a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"building, a lake, or an area you want to highlight."}],"sections":[],"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNEmptyFeature","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPoint","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygon","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolygonFeature","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolyline","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolylineFeature","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMultiPolylineFeature","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointAnnotation","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollectionFeature","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolyline","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolylineFeature","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeCollection","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeCollectionFeature"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Shapes","title":"Shapes"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre"]]},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPolygon/interiorPolygons":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"interiorPolygons","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolygon\/interiorpolygons","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPolygon\/interiorPolygons","title":"interiorPolygons","abstract":[{"text":"The array of polygons nested inside the receiver.","type":"text"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNMapView/addOverlay:":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"text","text":"- "},{"